-- Russian Grain Yields in 11 Areas Will Fall 30% on Worst Drought in Decade
-- Maria Kolesnikova
-- 2010-07-12T05:10:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/russian-grain-yields-in-11-areas-will-fall-30-on-worst-drought-in-decade.html

          
          
             Grain yields in 11 Russian regions
will fall at least 30 percent this year as the worst drought in
a decade damages crops, the Federal Hydrometeorological Service
said on its website.  
 The regions are mainly in the Ural Mountains and Volga
River regions.  
